An alternative would be [String.format(String, Object...)](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/String.html#format(java.lang.String,java.lang.Object...)), where the first parameter is always the format (e.g. `&quot;%f&quot;`) and the rest are the parameters to format. The format string itself could contain text as well and you can format multiple parameters. It&#39;s syntax is documented [here](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/util/Formatter.html#syntax).

